(Description)
Given an integer num, repeatedly add all its digits until the result has only one digit, and return it.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public int addDigits(int num) {
        if (num == 0) {
            return 0;
        }
        else if (num % 9 == 0) {
            return 9;
        }
        else {
            return num % 9;
        }
    }
}

--- Approach ---
When calculating a digit nums, they follow one special rule, that is repeating of 9.
- (1 ~ 9), digital root grow by 1,
- when it is over 9, at 10, digital root get back to the 1.
- (10 ~ 18), digital root grow by 1 again.
- Then, it is over 18, hitting 19, digital root become 1 again.

So that, the algorithm returns under the rule, the digital nums are same with the mod of number 9.
